        >
          <h2 style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 700">
            Saudi Fund Trims Nintendo Stake While Eyeing More
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-oct-9-1.jpg"
          alt="Saudi Fund Trims Nintendo Stake While Eyeing More"
        />
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="EB Garamond"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <p
            style="
              font-size: 18px;
              line-height: 1.6;
            "
          >Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund (PIF) trimmed its Nintendo stake to <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/2024/10/08/saudi-fund-trims-nintendo-stake-after-saying-it-wants-more/" target="_blank">7.54%</a> but hinted at deploying more capital into the gaming giant. Despite trimming its holdings, PIF remains a top Nintendo shareholder, reflecting its broader push to diversify beyond oil and build an entertainment hub. This move aligns with PIF’s $38 billion gaming strategy, targeting companies across Japan and Korea. While the sale may be a portfolio adjustment, PIF’s long-term goal of deepening ties with gaming companies seems intact.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding-top="20px"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
